[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man, 69, arrested after pensioner dies in road collision

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorist has been arrested after a pensioner died following a road collision.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Ian Whitworth, 80, was pronounced dead shortly after the incident at about 22:10 GMT on Friday in Cheadle Hulme, Stockport.
A 69-year-old man has been arrested by Greater Manchester Police on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving and failing to stop at the scene.
He remains in custody following a police appeal for information.
